description:
This is a collection of video documentaries and literature regarding the subject of poisonous dental &quot;silver&quot; (amalgam) fillings which are 50 percent mercury, a known neurodegenerative toxic metal.  Beware amalgam dental fillings!  They may soon (hopefully) be banned for use in all civilized countries.

The two center pieces here are the TV documentaries &quot;Is there poison in your mouth,&quot; aired by 60 Minutes on CBS in 1990 (25 minutes) and &quot;Poison in the Mouth,&quot; aired by Panorama on the BBC in 1994 (38 minutes).

The other three videos are two short previews and a brief introduction to the subject of mercury neurotoxicity released by the University of Calgary.  The previews are for two documentaries which you can purchase at www.lammag.com, &quot;Quecksilber - The Strange Story of Dental Amalgam&quot; and &quot;Rooted&quot; about the dangers of root canals.

The collection of .pdf and .doc files are a small sample of the written literature on this subject, all of which is available on the web.  All 5 of the videos can be found on Google or Youtube.

